= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =
configset listname unsubscribe_policy = VALUE
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Value must be: open, or closed, or auto
Default Value: open
Data Type    : enum
Variable Type: majordomo,access,subscribe
Apply to List: regular lists, but not the GLOBAL pseudo-list
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset listname unsubscribe_policy = open

(text above is from configshow, Mj2 0.1199902200, extracted 12 Apr 1999)


One of three values: open, closed, auto.  Open allows people to
unsubscribe themselves from the list.  Auto allows anybody to
unsubscribe anybody to the list without maintainer approval.  Closed
requires maintainer approval for all unsubscribe requests to the list.

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
